---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'safetywing', text: 'SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'worldnomads', text: 'World Nomads', level: 2 },
  { id: 'img-global', text: 'IMG Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-differences', text: 'Coverage Differences', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Travel Insurance Guide', href: '/guides/travel-insurance-vs-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'Budget Insurance', href: '/best/budget-insurance' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'worldnomads', header: 'World Nomads' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Insurance Type', safetywing: 'Travel medical', worldnomads: 'Travel insurance', img: 'Short-term health' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', safetywing: '$250,000', worldnomads: '$100K-250K', img: '$1M - $5M' },
  { feature: 'Trip Duration', safetywing: 'Unlimited', worldnomads: 'Up to 1 year', img: 'Up to 2 years' },
  { feature: 'Adventure Sports', safetywing: 'Limited', worldnomads: 'Excellent', img: 'Basic' },
  { feature: 'Trip Cancellation', safetywing: 'No', worldnomads: 'Yes', img: 'No' },
  { feature: 'Baggage Coverage', safetywing: 'No', worldnomads: 'Yes', img: 'No' },
  { feature: 'Flexibility', safetywing: 'Monthly', worldnomads: 'Trip-based', img: 'Annual/6-month' },
  { feature: 'Best For', safetywing: 'Digital nomads', worldnomads: 'Adventure trips', img: 'Longer stays' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'scenario', header: 'Scenario' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
  { key: 'worldnomads', header: 'World Nomads' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { scenario: '1 Month, Age 30', safetywing: '$45-55', worldnomads: '$80-150', img: '$80-120' },
  { scenario: '3 Months, Age 30', safetywing: '$135-165', worldnomads: '$200-350', img: '$200-300' },
  { scenario: '6 Months, Age 30', safetywing: '$270-330', worldnomads: '$350-600', img: '$400-550' },
  { scenario: '12 Months, Age 30', safetywing: '$540-660', worldnomads: '$600-1,000', img: '$750-1,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing vs World Nomads vs IMG: Best Short-Term Travel Insurance 2026"
  description="Compare short-term coverage options: SafetyWing, World Nomads, and IMG Global. From weekend trips to year-long adventures—find the right temporary insurance."
  headline="SafetyWing vs World Nomads vs IMG: Short-Term Coverage Compared"
  subheadline="Three approaches to temporary coverage—nomad-focused, adventure-focused, and health-focused. Here's how to choose for trips from weeks to months."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border-2 border-amber-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best for Nomads</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">SafetyWing</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">$45/mo. Monthly subscription. No end date required. Best for ongoing travel without fixed plans.</p>
      <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best for Adventure</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">World Nomads</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best adventure sports coverage. Includes trip cancellation and baggage. Traditional travel insurance.</p>
      <a href="/go/world-nomads" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get World Nomads Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Health Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">IMG Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Real health insurance for 6-24 months. Higher limits. Best for gap year or extended stays.</p>
      <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    These three serve different needs: SafetyWing is flexible month-to-month coverage for nomads. World Nomads is traditional travel insurance with trip benefits. IMG is actual short-term health insurance for longer stays. Pick based on your trip type and duration.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="safetywing">SafetyWing</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Monthly Billing</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">No End Date</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Cheapest</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    SafetyWing's Nomad Insurance is unique: it's a subscription you can start and stop anytime. No need to specify an end date. At $45/month, it's the cheapest option for ongoing coverage. Perfect for digital nomads with flexible schedules.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Only $45/month starting price</li>
    <li>Monthly subscription—cancel anytime</li>
    <li>No end date required</li>
    <li>Covers 180+ countries</li>
    <li>30 days home country coverage per 90 days</li>
    <li>Simple online signup</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Travel medical, not health insurance</li>
    <li>$250K limit (low for serious illness)</li>
    <li>Limited adventure sports coverage</li>
    <li>No trip cancellation or baggage</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions excluded</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Digital nomads with no fixed plans. Budget travelers who want basic coverage. Anyone who needs flexibility to extend or end coverage.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/safetywing" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get SafetyWing Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/safetywing" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="worldnomads">World Nomads</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Adventure Sports</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Trip Benefits</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Traditional Travel</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    World Nomads is traditional travel insurance designed for adventurers. It covers activities most insurers exclude—skiing, scuba diving, rock climbing. Plus trip cancellation, baggage loss, and travel delays. Best for active trips with defined dates.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Best adventure sports coverage (150+ activities)</li>
    <li>Trip cancellation included</li>
    <li>Baggage loss/delay coverage</li>
    <li>Emergency evacuation</li>
    <li>Can buy while already traveling</li>
    <li>24/7 assistance</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>More expensive than SafetyWing</li>
    <li>Trip-based (need end date)</li>
    <li>Lower medical limits ($100-250K)</li>
    <li>Not designed for extended stays</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions excluded</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Adventure travelers. Backpackers doing risky activities. Anyone who needs trip cancellation and baggage coverage. Trips with fixed dates.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/world-nomads" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get World Nomads Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/world-nomads" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="img-global">IMG Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Real Health Insurance</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Higher Limits</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">6-24 Months</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    IMG Global offers actual short-term health insurance—not travel insurance. Higher limits ($1-5M), better coverage, designed for stays of 6-24 months. The bridge between travel insurance and full expat health plans. Best for gap years or extended trips.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Real health insurance, not travel medical</li>
    <li>Up to $5M coverage limits</li>
    <li>Covers stays up to 2 years</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions considered</li>
    <li>Routine care options available</li>
    <li>Better claims experience</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>More expensive than travel insurance</li>
    <li>Minimum 6-month commitment typical</li>
    <li>No trip cancellation or baggage</li>
    <li>Limited adventure sports</li>
    <li>Requires application/underwriting</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Gap year travelers. Extended sabbaticals. Anyone staying 6+ months who wants real health coverage. Those transitioning to longer-term expat life.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/img-global" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get IMG Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/img-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Short-Term Options"
    description="Get quotes from all three to find the right coverage for your trip length and activities."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    SafetyWing is cheapest for ongoing coverage. World Nomads costs more but includes trip benefits. IMG is most expensive but provides the most comprehensive health coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated prices for healthy 30-year-old. World Nomads varies significantly by activities covered. Excludes US coverage for all.
  </p>

  <h2 id="coverage-differences">Understanding the Coverage Differences</h2>

  <h3>Medical Coverage</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Emergency medical only. $250K limit. Hospital and doctor visits for accidents/illness.</li>
    <li><strong>World Nomads:</strong> Emergency medical only. $100-250K limits. Similar to SafetyWing but with trip benefits.</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance. Up to $5M limits. Includes preventive care options.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Adventure Sports</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Basic coverage. Excludes most extreme sports.</li>
    <li><strong>World Nomads:</strong> Excellent—covers 150+ activities including skiing, scuba, bungee jumping.</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Limited adventure coverage. May need add-ons for specific activities.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Trip Benefits</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> None. Medical only.</li>
    <li><strong>World Nomads:</strong> Trip cancellation, baggage loss, delays, missed connections.</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> None. Health coverage only.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Duration Flexibility</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Most flexible—monthly subscription, no end date.</li>
    <li><strong>World Nomads:</strong> Trip-based—specify dates, can extend while traveling.</li>
    <li><strong>IMG:</strong> Term-based—6-24 month commitments typical.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose SafetyWing if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are a digital nomad with no fixed plans</li>
        <li>Want month-to-month flexibility</li>
        <li>Are on a tight budget</li>
        <li>Just need basic emergency coverage</li>
        <li>Don't need trip cancellation or baggage</li>
        <li>Want to start coverage immediately</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose World Nomads if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Plan to do adventure activities</li>
        <li>Need trip cancellation coverage</li>
        <li>Want baggage protection</li>
        <li>Have a defined trip with dates</li>
        <li>Are going backpacking or on an adventure trip</li>
        <li>Already invested in expensive flights/bookings</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose IMG Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are staying 6+ months in one place</li>
        <li>Want real health insurance, not travel medical</li>
        <li>Need higher coverage limits</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions to consider</li>
        <li>Want routine care coverage options</li>
        <li>Are transitioning toward expat life</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Can I buy coverage after my trip has started?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing: Yes, instantly. World Nomads: Yes, with some restrictions. IMG: Generally needs to be purchased before departure. If you're already traveling, SafetyWing or World Nomads are your options.
  </p>

  <h3>Which is best for a 3-month trip?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on activities. For adventure activities, World Nomads. For budget coverage, SafetyWing. For comprehensive health, IMG (though they prefer longer terms). Most 3-month travelers choose SafetyWing or World Nomads.
  </p>

  <h3>Do any cover pre-existing conditions?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing and World Nomads: No. IMG: May cover stable conditions after underwriting. If you have pre-existing conditions and need short-term coverage, IMG is your best option, though coverage isn't guaranteed.
  </p>

  <h3>What about COVID-19 coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    All three cover COVID-19 like any other illness. Testing, treatment, and hospitalization are covered under medical benefits. Some plans include quarantine coverage. Verify current terms as COVID policies evolve.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I extend my coverage while traveling?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing: Yes, automatic—just keep paying. World Nomads: Yes, can extend trip dates online. IMG: Depends on plan—some allow extension, others require new application.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Coverage terms and prices change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify current benefits directly with each provider before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
